---
import Base from "../../../layouts/Base.astro";

const title = "SplatForge — QAT-Scaffold (lossless 50%) API";
const description =
  "Quant-Aware Retrain compression for Scaffold-GS PLYs. ~50% size reduction with a mean +0.172 dB PSNR gain across 6 Mip-NeRF 360 scenes (bonsai, bicycle, garden, stump, treehill, flowers). Bit-exact reconstruction. Free tier: 1 scene/day under 100 MB. Paid tier: $0.50/GB processed, no daily cap.";

const apiBase = import.meta.env.PUBLIC_API_BASE ?? "https://api.splatforge.com";
---

<Base title={title} description={description}>
  <nav class="nav" aria-label="Primary">
    <a href="/" class="nav-brand">
      <span class="dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>
      splatforge
    </a>
    <div class="nav-links">
      <a href="/#docs">Quickstart</a>
      <a href="/bench">SplatBench</a>
      <a href="/import">Import</a>
      <a href="/#try" aria-current="page">Try it</a>
    </div>
  </nav>

  <h1>QAT-Scaffold preset (lossless 50%)</h1>
  <p class="lede">
    The <code>splatforge-qat-scaffold</code> preset compresses
    Scaffold-GS PLYs in half with a <strong>mean +0.172 dB PSNR
    gain</strong> measured across six Mip-NeRF 360 scenes.
    Reconstruction is bit-exact relative to the retrained Scaffold
    checkpoint that the codec produces — the dB delta is vs the
    un-retrained Scaffold-GS baseline (the retrain pass is part of
    the codec, not a separate quality knob).
  </p>

  <h2>Validated numbers (2026-05-16, N=1 per scene)</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Scene</th>
        <th>Size reduction</th>
        <th>Delta PSNR vs Scaffold baseline</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td>bonsai</td><td>~50%</td><td>+0.17 dB</td></tr>
      <tr><td>bicycle</td><td>~50%</td><td>+0.04 dB</td></tr>
      <tr><td>garden</td><td>~50%</td><td>+0.31 dB</td></tr>
      <tr><td>stump</td><td>~50%</td><td>+0.15 dB</td></tr>
      <tr><td>treehill</td><td>~50%</td><td>+0.18 dB</td></tr>
      <tr><td>flowers</td><td>~50%</td><td>+0.18 dB</td></tr>
      <tr>
        <td><strong>Mean (6 scenes)</strong></td>
        <td><strong>~50%</strong></td>
        <td><strong>+0.172 dB</strong></td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
  <p class="footnote">
    Per-scene N=1 today. N&gt;=3 multi-seed re-run scheduled; the
    Principle-2 render-PSNR gate is already cleared at N=1 because the
    minimum scene delta (<code>+0.04 dB</code> on bicycle) is positive.
  </p>

  <h2>Endpoint</h2>
  <pre><code>POST {apiBase}/v1/jobs
Authorization: Bearer &lt;api_key&gt;
Content-Type: application/json

&#123;
  "preset": "splatforge-qat-scaffold",
  "blob_url": "https://blob.vercel-storage.com/uploads/&lt;sha&gt;-scaffold.ply",
  "filename": "scaffold.ply"
&#125;</code></pre>

  <h2>Auth</h2>
  <p>
    Every request needs <code>Authorization: Bearer &lt;api_key&gt;</code>.
    New accounts get a free-tier key via the existing self-serve flow at
    <a href="/pricing#signup">/pricing</a> (Stripe Checkout submits the
    email, the webhook issues a key, the dashboard and the receipt
    email both show the key). No separate QAT-Scaffold signup; the
    same key gates this preset.
  </p>

  <h2>Request / response</h2>
  <p>
    Same job shape as every other preset — the only field that changes
    is <code>preset</code>. The API returns a <code>job_id</code>
    immediately and POSTs the terminal result to your registered
    callback (or you can poll <code>GET /v1/jobs/&lt;job_id&gt;</code>).
  </p>
  <pre><code>// 202 Accepted
&#123;
  "job_id": "01HZ9X2P8E4QXM6R0M3T7G1K8C",
  "preset": "splatforge-qat-scaffold",
  "status": "queued",
  "estimated_compute_seconds": 360,
  "estimated_cost_usd_cents": 18
&#125;

// terminal callback (or GET /v1/jobs/&lt;id&gt;)
&#123;
  "job_id": "01HZ9X2P8E4QXM6R0M3T7G1K8C",
  "status": "done",
  "output_url": "https://blob.vercel-storage.com/outputs/&lt;sha&gt;-qat.ply",
  "size_bytes_in":  136847392,
  "size_bytes_out":  68205184,
  "ratio": 2.006,
  "delta_psnr_db": 0.17
&#125;</code></pre>

  <h2>Input shapes</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>
      A <strong>Scaffold-GS PLY</strong> (single file). The encoder
      reads the standard Scaffold attribute layout —
      <code>f_anchor_feat</code>, <code>f_offset</code>,
      <code>scale</code>, <code>rotation</code>, <code>opacity</code> —
      and rejects vanilla 3DGS PLYs with a clear error. Use the
      <code>hacpp-lzma</code> preset if you have a Scaffold bundle
      (PLY + MLP weights) instead of a flat PLY.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Output shape</h2>
  <p>
    A single compressed <code>.ply</code> roughly half the size of the
    input. The file is self-contained: any Scaffold-GS-aware decoder
    can render it because the quantized streams are stored in
    standard PLY-attribute slots with documented quant scales in the
    header comment.
  </p>

  <h2>Rate limits</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Tier</th><th>Per-key request budget</th><th>Per-input size</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><strong>Free</strong></td>
        <td>1 scene / 24 h</td>
        <td>&lt;= 100 MB Scaffold PLY</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><strong>Paid</strong></td>
        <td>No daily cap</td>
        <td>No size cap (subject to Modal-side timeouts on enormous
        captures — talk to us if you have a &gt;5 GB Scaffold)</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
  <p>
    Rate limits are enforced per-key by the existing
    <code>splatforge_rate_limit</code> middleware (PR #33). Free-tier
    overage returns <code>HTTP 429</code> with a
    <code>X-Free-Tier-Reset</code> header pointing at the next
    midnight UTC window.
  </p>

  <h2>Pricing</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Free tier:</strong> 1 scene/day, &lt;= 100 MB input. No
      card required. Sign up at <a href="/pricing#signup">/pricing</a>.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Paid tier:</strong> <code>$0.50 / GB processed</code>.
      Billed monthly via Stripe. No flat fee, no minimum, no daily
      cap. A typical 130 MB Scaffold PLY costs ~$0.065 / scene.
    </li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Use <code>POST /v1/pricing/preview</code> with
    <code>&#123; "size_bytes": &lt;n&gt;, "preset": "splatforge-qat-scaffold" &#125;</code>
    to get a quote before submitting the job. The preview returns the
    same shape as the rest of the pricing surface.
  </p>

  <h2>Worker dispatch</h2>
  <p>
    The public worker forwards every <code>splatforge-qat-scaffold</code>
    enqueue to a private Modal app. The operator sets
    <code>SPLATFORGE_QAT_SCAFFOLD_URL</code> in the
    <code>splatforge-preset-urls</code> Modal secret to wire the route;
    <code>GET /healthz</code> on the worker exposes a
    <code>preset_dispatch_configured.splatforge-qat-scaffold</code>
    bool so deploys are verifiable without inspecting secrets.
  </p>

  <h2>Anti-claims</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Not a vanilla 3DGS codec.</strong> The compression only
      works on Scaffold-GS PLYs because it leans on the anchor-feature
      + offset structure. Use <code>fcgs-instant</code> or
      <code>hacpp-lzma</code> for non-Scaffold inputs.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Bit-exact != "lossless at the photo level".</strong>
      The compressed PLY decodes to exactly the same Scaffold tensors
      the retrain step produces. The +0.17 dB headline is vs the
      un-retrained Scaffold baseline because the retrain pass is part
      of the codec — if you compare to your own retrained checkpoint
      the delta is zero.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>N&gt;=3 multi-seed pending.</strong> All six scenes
      cleared Principle 2 at N=1 (minimum delta +0.04 dB &gt; 0);
      multi-seed stats follow in the next research drop.
    </li>
  </ul>
</Base>
